Subject: [PATCH 2/2] wasm: expose outputBuffer pointer + dimensions to JS
Author: pi-extension-gba vendor-builder

The shipped build has no JS-callable pixel-read API (see V2 in
docs/verify/V1-V2-V7.md). Calling Module.screenshot() writes a PNG
into the Emscripten VFS -- re-encoding per frame inside the WASM is
far too slow for a 30 fps render loop. We need direct access to the
RGBA bytes the core has already written.

mGBA's Emscripten renderer keeps a single outputBuffer (pointer stored
on struct mEmscriptenRenderer) that renderer->core->setVideoBuffer is
pointed at inside loadGame() (main.c). The core writes into it each
emulated frame in ABGR8888 format (SDL_PIXELFORMAT_ABGR8888, which is
RGBA little-endian byte order: byte 0 = R, 1 = G, 2 = B, 3 = A). The
format is a direct match for fast-png / upng-js.

This patch adds five EMSCRIPTEN_KEEPALIVE accessors in main.c:

  uint8_t* getPixelBuffer(void)        -- pointer to outputBuffer
  int      getPixelBufferSize(void)    -- width*height*BYTES_PER_PIXEL
  int      getPixelBufferStride(void)  -- bytes per row
  int      getPixelBufferWidth(void)   -- current video width (GBA=240)
  int      getPixelBufferHeight(void)  -- current video height (GBA=160)

Wraps them in pre.js as:

  Module.getPixelBuffer() -> Uint8Array  (view into HEAPU8, NOT a copy;
                                          callers that need to persist
                                          across stepFrames must .slice())
  Module.getPixelBufferDimensions() -> { width, height, stride }

And appends TS declarations to mgba.d.ts.

The pointer is stable for the lifetime of the currently-loaded ROM --
loadGame() re-allocates the SDL texture on ROM switch, so callers must
re-read the pointer after loadGame. During steady-state play the
pointer does not move.

Apply with: patch -p1 < 0002-export-getPixelBuffer.patch
Base commit: thenick775/mgba @ be30a34e913da1ba7f040d3db4e10f700ce49f76
Depends on: 0001-add-node-environment.patch for HEAPU8 export.

---
